cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper deals with deep neural network compression for image classification and object detection, which are both subfields of computer vision (CV). Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of clustering algorithms, which falls under machine learning (ML) and specifically, unsupervised learning. Hence, cs.LG and cs.AI are also likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with reducing computational cost and memory footprint, which are related to hardware and optimization, respectively. Therefore, cs.NE and cs.MM are also possible sub-categories.
